  "body": "## Issue\r\n\r\nTruffle doesn't support ESM.\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Set `\"type\": \"module\"` in `package.json`.\r\n2. Run truffle.\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nThe config loads, and ESM imports are correctly handled.\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\nThe configuration doesn't load, because the `original-require` package which ingests `truffle-config.js` uses `require` and not `import`.\r\nThe error suggests to change the extension to `.cjs`, but this just causes a cascade of needing to change extensions until the entire project is `.cjs` files and no longer a module.\r\n\r\nIt's impossible to use latest versions of popular tools such as `node-fetch` which have switched over to ESM, and it's causing dependency rot.\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: Linux (Fedora)\r\n* Ethereum client: N/A\r\n* Truffle version: 5.4.12\r\n* node version: 16.5.0\r\n* npm version: 7.19.1\r\n",
